Five suspects in Sh20,300,000 motorcycles theft case were yesterday charged at a Kibera court.  Jibril Hassan Edin, Issack Hassan Ibrahim, Rooney Jahwan Elisha, Stephen Munga Iogo and Kelvin Omboke Otieno denied the charges before Kibera Senior Principal Magistrate Renee Kitagwa, who ordered that they be detained at the Capitol Hill Police Station.  They are charged with stealing 169 motorcycles in Nairobi county from Mugo Auto Kenya on diverse dates between January 2021 and September 2021. The case will be heard on Monday.   Kisumu 'Boda Boda' Motion targeting women riders By Mireri Junior | 45 minutes ago By Julius Chepkwony | 1 hour ago By Josphat Thiongâ€™o | 5 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 14 hours ago